txt.en: Collect fresh fish from the docks ([placeholder]/[placeholder])
Anírwen is at the market near the docks of Dol Amroth, on the eastern side of the city.\n\nYou should bring the fresh catch to Anírwen.
'Ah! Much faster than my usual worker. Thank you, [placeholder]. My, but you are helpful.'
Collected fresh fish from the docks ([placeholder]/[placeholder])

'You look like a stout and trustworthy sort! How would you like to earn a few pence? My usual delivery-boy hasn't showed up today, and I need someone to haul in today's catch.\n\n'You can find fresh fish by the ships parked at the pier. If you bring me today's catch, I'll pay you what I pay my normal worker.'
Anírwen has asked you to collect the catch from today and bring it to the fish market.
Today's catch of fresh fish can be found along the piers where the boats are parked in the wharf of Dol Amroth.\n\nYou should pick up the fresh fish from the wharf, and bring it to Anírwen.
